$interpreted: Puggi: ...*cough*...*cough*...!
Joan: Master! Are you okay?
Puggi: Thank Sdorica I'm the only really important character in this Sdori...ca. There's no way they'd let anything bad happen to me.
Puggi: Without me, how would they hold holiday events?
Joan: (My God, master has been locked up for so long that his brain has turned to mush...)
Joan: As long as it's nothing serious, that's all that really matters~
Puggi: ...Oof!!
Joan: Master! What is it?
Puggi: Pressure...in my chest...
Joan: Forgive me...it's my fault that the casino snatched you up in the first place...
Joan: Master, does it hurt here? Or here? Was the rope tied too tightly?
Puggi: Don't know...my whole body hurts. Quick! Massage my body before it's too late~
Joan: No problem!
Joan: How's this?
Puggi: Mmmm...your bosom smells so good. So fragrant～
Joan: Huh? What's that? Fragrant?
Puggi: Painful! I said it's so painful!!
Joan: But you're the master of love! You cannot die!
Puggi: Quick...must...hold me tight...
Casino Bodyguard: Found 'em!
Joan: You've been following us all along?
Experienced Bodyguard: That's right. All the way from the casino. We saw it all. You're the Thief of the Gleaming Star!
Casino Bodyguard: At last, we've seen the face behind the mask! Now you better come with us!
Joan: (They've been this persistent...just to see my face...)
Joan: (I wonder if they like me?)
Experienced Bodyguard: Cut the crap. You're coming with us.
Joan: You're in quite a rush, huh?
Experienced Bodyguard: Rats...never thought she'd be this tough...
Joan: What a pity...I don't like guys that work at casinos.
Joan: Forgive me for causing you to fall for me. Alas! What kind of woman am I...?
Casino Bodyguard: Uhhhh...I think there's been a misunderstanding. We're here for the croissant.
Joan: (Lordie lord is that a handsome fella~~~! Blonde hair, blue eyes...just like a prince from a romance novel!)
Edward: My fair lady, I hope these brutes didn't frighten you.
Joan: I-I-I-I-I'm fine...
Puggi: Who gave you permission to kiss!!!!
Puggi: You jump in after they surrender and now you're acting like some knight in shining armor! You think I'm an idiot! Joan, let's go honey!
Edward: Ah, your name is Joan. What a beautiful name.
Joan: Thank...thank you.
Joan: Oh! My gosh...I'm not wearing any make-up——
Joan: I usually go all natural, but today it's a little much...
Joan: If they didn't come busting out of nowhere, I'd have time to change...
Edward: You've no need for make-up. Perhaps I should thank those brutes...after all, seeing you like that was so......captivating.
Edward: ...Well then, I must be on my way.
Puggi: Hey! Who authorized this?
Puggi: Background actors are not allowed to steal the show from the star!!
Joan: Master, I feel dizzy...
Puggi: You poor thing, you must have been terrified by that ghastly fellow.
Joan: My face...it's so hot...
Puggi: No, no, no. It's this place, much too hot. Let's go cool off over there.
Joan: My heart...it's pounding.
Puggi: Face is red, heart is racing...oh no!! Joan, my lady, could it be...
Joan: What should I do? Am I going to die?
Puggi: My God. It's much worse than that. You're...
Puggi: ...in love!!!
